reviews.review: If you are a true fan of the Star Wars universe you will love this movie.   If youre a casual fan it may not be for you.  No matter what, its entertaining.

I'm going to say what so many others have said - WOW! Great action, special effects, story, and tying-up loose ends. I know the story didn't make everyone happy, but it settled enough plot lines to satisfy me, even though some were a bit of a stretch. A multi-generational saga, which has lasted most of my adult like, has finally ended. Time to move on.

A solid ending for the Star Wars saga. They took some things in a different direction than expected after the last film and there were a few weird little things that didn't make sense to me, but over all a fantastic film.

A complete lack of imagination drives this movie. Moviegoers still looking to blame Rian Johnson for deconstructing their favorite movie mythology should really look to JJ Abrams here for the blame - this story constantly trips over itself trying to reference  scenes and imagery you've seen before, without saying anything new or of substance. This was a really bad movie.

Absolutely one of the best Star Wars movies I've ever seen and a great finish to a chapter by Disney. Don't listen to the critics this movie has so many hints at previous Star Wars films and similarities compared to older Star Wars movies it is is definitely a must see and one of my top 3 ever Star Wars films!
The movie was awesome, it was 1000 times better then the last Jedi. Thank you very much DISNEY for bringing back J.J. Abrams.
Best movie in the sequel trilogy. A lot more creative than the force awakens and corrected to some extent the complete disaster created by Johnson.
Gave me everything I wanted from a star wars movie.  Fantastic scenery, killer action, camaraderie between the main characters and just some old school star wars feels.  Well done!
I thought it was a wild and crazy ride. It really brought the new trilogy together for me and made things fall into place. I thoroughly enjoyed it and will most likely go to see it again soon.
Its star wars. Whats not to like!
